	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Bottom line, people who can't cast this spell have no idea of it's potential. So I'm suprised by all the non-wiz posts and by non-lure level wizard posts. (Well we do get Enticement of Flame at lower levels...so...).  Anyway, Lures can be resisted under several instances. When:<BR>
1) The mob is high resist against that class of spell (fire, cold, magic). In other words, Lure of Ice won't work on Cold based dragons, even with ench, shaman, cleric and bard debuffs.<BR>
2) When the mob is very highly buffed. In other words, you sometimes see partial resists to full resists until the mob is seriously debuffed.<BR>
3) When the mob is levels higher than you. In other words, on the very highest level mobs (ones that are still red to you at level 60). You may get occasional resists.  Debuffs are key.<BR>
<BR>
There are resist tables on graffe.com I believe that will tell you yer odds of having fire, cold, magic (non-lure and lure) hit on many of the higher level mobs.  Some of the nastiest dragons will resist lure spells quite often...even when you're level 60.<BR>
<BR>
Thankfully Porlo's Fury was implimented for Dragons and Hsagra's Wrath for giants.  These truly are totally unresistable....always.  But, you have to learn how to use them as there is high agro when you hit for 2000dd.  Also, they cost 2 peridots per cast.<BR>
<BR>
Believe me, all 60th wizards want and need this wonderful spell and wait anxiously for it to drop as it's fairly uncommon on uber mobs to drop most of the wizzie spells.<BR>
<BR>
Meekee 60th Sorcerer<BR>
Ring of Shadows<BR>
Veeshan
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
