	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Okay I have to make some things clear to people that are unaware of what EQ is like post 50.<BR>
<BR>
Post 50 here is the brutal, terrible, simple, truth, in a *big* raid when you get to the UBER mobs that are the focus of the raid (Statues of Rallos Zek, GODs, Velketor, et al) then there are realy TWO classes that are important, warriors, and clerics.<BR>
<BR>
Now some classes :Rangers, Paladins, Monks, Rogues are important too because they can do melee dmg (the rogues and monks can do quite a bit) and won't get the mobs aggrod on them because they presumably will have several experienced warriors making sure they take all the hits, while the clerics focus on healing the player that is the focus of the mobs *brutal* onslaught.<BR>
<BR>
That's basically what a melee is going to be doing, now lets talk about casters:<BR>
<BR>
Druids: buff before fight, maybe a heal if someone is taking a little AoE damage, might try some DD spells, but more than likely you will get resisted every time.<BR>
<BR>
Mage: Send in the pets, only 4 will be on the mob so unless you have the epic or a good focus item you might not even get to do this, you could try DD, and yours might hit but it's doubtful.<BR>
<BR>
Necro: Simple, feed mana to clerics. YOU WILL NEVER GET TO USE YOUR PET, YOU WILL NEVER USE YOUR DOTS OR DDs. Because they WILL NOT, UNDER ANY CIRCUMSTANCES work on the uber mobs like trakanon , or the gods. Your only job is to feed mana to clerics.<BR>
<BR>
Wizard: Well once the melees have bashed the mob down to under 50% (some groups choose a diff percentage) you get to cast your nukes, mainly nukes like this that aren't going to be resisted, you do this to finish the fight quicker (the clerics mana can only hold out so long, and when the clerics all start going oom, the tanks die very fast, then everyone evacs or dies) which is why this is of some importance, although good planners bring enough clerics to make sure this won't happen so much.<BR>
<BR>
I won't mention the other classes because I'm tired of typing, I just thought I'd illustrate that all those great DDs that everyone gets are going to be like spitwads. I have a 60 necro, and on the uber mobs, I'm a mana battery.<BR>
<BR>
Now this isn't saying classes like the necro aren't good, they just can't do dmg to the uber mobs, they can still do great against the regular mobs (basically anything that's not a god or anything thats not a lvl 65+ and 70+ velious mob.)<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
